Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters. Product: QBO Description: How the name of the customer should be presented, e.g. on credit cards.
If you do not provide any value, the value of the Name attribute is used. If Name is not specified, the value of the GivenName and FamilyName attributes are used.
For example, if the name of the customer is John Doe and you specify a value for ShowAs, such as John, the ShowAs contains John in the return value. If you do not specify any value for ShowAs, the ShowAs contains John Doe in the return value.

For example: "Retail:Clothing".

attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the SalesTaxCode object. Product: QBO Description: QBO only supports the customers or jobs being taxable or not, so if this field is "1", the job is taxable. If the field value is null, the job is not taxable. All other values are invalid.
Note that if you have specified a TaxAmt and TaxRate, SalesTaxCodeId will be "1" even if you don't specify it directly. To make SalesTaxCodeId not taxable, TaxAmt and TaxRate must be null.

attributes.name: SalesTaxCodeName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Name for the SalesTaxCode.
Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters. Product: QBO Description: Indicates if the customer or job is taxable. The only valid value is "IS_TAXABLE" indicating the job is taxable. If the field value is null, the job is not taxable. Use SalesTaxCodeId to set the value. This is a read-only field.

A reference to the Account is required for the Create operation, either the AccountId or AccountName; AccountId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: Account ID that is associated with the line item.
Account ID is an optional output-only field for the Item based expense.
Account ID is required for the account-based expense.
The account is of the basic five types: Income, Expense, Asset, Liability, Owner equity.
Optional for Item.IncomeAccountRef.AccountId, IncomeAccountRef is specified for sales items. If it is not specified, then the default income account ID from the company's preferences is used.
Optional for Item.ExpenseAccountRef.AccountId, this indicates the expense account that is used to pay the vendor for this item. If this is a service item, it can also be an equity account to record a draw against the company equity to pay for the service. Required: ALL

For example, "Bad Debt:Loans to Burt".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. If DocNumber is not provided, and the Custom Transaction Number is set to "Off", QBO assigns a document number using the next-in-sequence algorithm for Sales transactions. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 11 characters; for Payment, Bill, ItemReceipt and VendorCredit, max. length: 20 characters. Required: QBW Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: TxnDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred. Often, it is the date when the transaction is created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects the financial statements. If the date is not supplied, the current date on the server is used.
For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. Often, but not required to be, the date the transaction was created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects financial statements. Required: QBW Filterable: ALL Sortable: QBO

For a Bill, this is the memo of the transaction to provide more detail, and does not appear in the printed message of the bill. The maximum length for Bill Msg is 4000 characters.
For a CreditCardCharge, this message appears in the printed record; maximum length is 4000 characters.
Not supported for BillPayment, JournalEntry or Payment. Product: QBW Description: User entered message to the customer.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

Product: QBW Description: The status of the associated transaction (the transaction types are described in the TxnTypeEnum). Depending on the transaction type the status may have different values. For example, Sales Transactions acceptable values are defined in PaymentStatusEnum. For Estimate, the values accepted are defined in EstimateStatusEnum, and for BuildAssembly the values are defined in the BuildAssemblyStatusEnum. Product: QBO Description: Supported for Estimate only. The Estimate status may be of the following values:
  • Pending (default)
  • Accepted
  • Rejected
  • Closed

attributes.name: VendorId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the Vendor object associated with the transaction.
A reference to the Vendor is required for the Create operation, either the VendorId or VendorName; VendorId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID of the Vendor object.
For TimeActivity, either the VendorId or the EmployeeId is required. Required: ALL Filterable: QBO Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: VendorName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for a vendor. A fully-qualified name starts with the name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub name; append a colon and sub name for each additional sub name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Rock Construction:Building Materials".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Vendor is required for the Create operation, either the VendorId or VendorName; VendorId is preferred.

attributes.name: BillEmail
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The email address to which this bill is/was sent.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: ReplyEmail
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The email address to which inquiries about the bill may be directed. (Also appropriate for paypal payments).
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: TotalAmt
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The total amount due, determined by taking the sum of all lines associated. This includes all charges, allowances, taxes, discounts, etc. In case of the "credit" transaction (e.g. Vendor Credit) represents the amount of the received credit. Read-only field. Product: QBW Description: The total amount due, determined by taking the sum of all lines associated. This includes all charges, allowances, taxes, discounts, etc. In case of the "credit" transaction (e.g. Vendor Credit) represents the amount of the received credit.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks. Filterable: QBW

attributes.name: APAccountId
attributes.synopsis:

						Description: ID for the APAccount object. A reference to the Accounts Payable account is required for the Create operation, either the APAccountId or APAccountName; APAccountId is preferred.
						Required: QBW

attributes.name: APAccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an Accounts Payable account. A fully-qualified name starts with the account name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub account name; append a colon and sub account name for each additional sub account (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. Most small businesses have a single AP account named "Accounts Payable"; for a sub account, the fully qualified name would be, for example, "Accounts Payable:Johnson Trust".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Accounts Payable account is required for the Create operation, either the APAccountId or APAccountName; APAccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. If DocNumber is not provided, and the Custom Transaction Number is set to "Off", QBO assigns a document number using the next-in-sequence algorithm for Sales transactions. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 11 characters; for Payment, Bill, ItemReceipt and VendorCredit, max. length: 20 characters. Required: QBW Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: TxnDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred. Often, it is the date when the transaction is created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects the financial statements. If the date is not supplied, the current date on the server is used.
For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. Often, but not required to be, the date the transaction was created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects financial statements. Required: QBW Filterable: ALL Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: Currency
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Currency code based on the ISO 4217 standard that is common to all amounts on the associated transaction.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Msg
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: For an Invoice, this is the user-entered message to the customer that does appear in the invoice, and does appear in the printed invoice. The maximum length for Invoice Msg is 1000 characters.
For a Bill, this is the memo of the transaction to provide more detail, and does not appear in the printed message of the bill. The maximum length for Bill Msg is 4000 characters.
For a CreditCardCharge, this message appears in the printed record; maximum length is 4000 characters.
Not supported for BillPayment, JournalEntry or Payment. Product: QBW Description: User entered message to the customer.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Note
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Describes the transaction; a private note for the organization that does not appear in the invoice or bill payment. For BillPayment, if payment is made through a check, this note is marked as a memo. The maximum length for Note is 4000 characters.
Not supported for Bill, CashPurchase, Check, or CreditCardCharge. Product: QBW Description: User-entered note about the transaction that does not appear on the invoice.

attributes.name: ItemId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the Item object. A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID for the Item object. Required for Item based expense. For CashPurchase, this is refereced as CashPurchaseLine.ItemId. The range of ItemType is defined in the ItemTypeEnum. If you do not provide the ItemId, the default Service item Id is used.
A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. All other line attributes would be ignored for this shipping line.
For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.
For TimeActivity, this is the Id of the ServiceItem that corresponds to the type of work performed. Required: ALL

Product: QBW Description: Total amount of the charges or discounts for the given line. Includes the charges and allowances, but it excludes the tax amount. Product: QBO Description: Total amount of the charges or discounts for the given line. Includes the charges and allowances, but it excludes the tax amount.
Required for BillPayment, Estimate, Invoice, JournalEntry, Payment, SalesReceipt. Required: QBO

attributes.name: ClassId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
			            Description: ID of the Class object.

attributes.name: ClassName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for a class. A fully-qualified name starts with the class name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub class name; append a colon and sub class name for each additional sub class (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Crop:Corn".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.name: ReimbursableInfo
attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
				                Description: Information about the Customer and actual Job or Project for which the expense must be reimbursed.

attributes.name: BillableStatus
attributes.synopsis: Product: ALL Description: Indicates the billable state of the amount of this line.

attributes.name: ItemId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the Item object. A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID for the Item object. Required for Item based expense. For CashPurchase, this is refereced as CashPurchaseLine.ItemId. The range of ItemType is defined in the ItemTypeEnum. If you do not provide the ItemId, the default Service item Id is used.
A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. All other line attributes would be ignored for this shipping line.
For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.
For TimeActivity, this is the Id of the ServiceItem that corresponds to the type of work performed. Required: ALL

attributes.name: ItemName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an item. A fully-qualified name starts with the name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub name; append a colon and sub name for each additional sub name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Discount:Sales:Labor Day".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred.

attributes.name: ItemType
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: Type is an item classification that specifies the use of this item.

attributes.name: UnitPrice
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
			            Description: Unit Price of the service or the item from the given line.
			            Product: QBO
			            Description: Unit Price of the service or the item from the given line. Supported for Item-based expense.

attributes.name: Qty
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
			            Description: Indicates the number of order items for the given line.
			            Product: QBO
			            Description: Indicates the number of order items for the given line. Supported for Item-based expense.

Product: QBW

attributes.name: UOMAbbrv
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW

attributes.name: OverrideItemAccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the OverrideItemAccount object. Product: QBO Description: Supported for Invoice only.
When you specify a deposit line, this field should contain the "deposit to" account id. Required only if ItemId = "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID", In all other cases, it is ignored.

attributes.name: OverrideItemAccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an override item account. A fully-qualified name starts with the name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub name; append a colon and sub name for each additional sub name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Misc Expenses:Tips".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.name: AccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The ID of the Account object.
A reference to the Account is required for the Create operation, either the AccountId or AccountName; AccountId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: Account ID that is associated with the line item.
Account ID is an optional output-only field for the Item based expense.
Account ID is required for the account-based expense.
The account is of the basic five types: Income, Expense, Asset, Liability, Owner equity.
Optional for Item.IncomeAccountRef.AccountId, IncomeAccountRef is specified for sales items. If it is not specified, then the default income account ID from the company's preferences is used.
Optional for Item.ExpenseAccountRef.AccountId, this indicates the expense account that is used to pay the vendor for this item. If this is a service item, it can also be an equity account to record a draw against the company equity to pay for the service. Required: ALL

attributes.name: AccountName

Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.synopsis:

Use the child fields below only with the BillPaymentCreditCard endpoint.
Do not use these fields with BillPayment.

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. If DocNumber is not provided, and the Custom Transaction Number is set to "Off", QBO assigns a document number using the next-in-sequence algorithm for Sales transactions. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 11 characters; for Payment, Bill, ItemReceipt and VendorCredit, max. length: 20 characters. Required: QBW Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: TxnDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred. Often, it is the date when the transaction is created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects the financial statements. If the date is not supplied, the current date on the server is used.
For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. Often, but not required to be, the date the transaction was created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects financial statements. Required: QBW Filterable: ALL Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: Currency
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Currency code based on the ISO 4217 standard that is common to all amounts on the associated transaction.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Msg
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: For an Invoice, this is the user-entered message to the customer that does appear in the invoice, and does appear in the printed invoice. The maximum length for Invoice Msg is 1000 characters.
For a Bill, this is the memo of the transaction to provide more detail, and does not appear in the printed message of the bill. The maximum length for Bill Msg is 4000 characters.
For a CreditCardCharge, this message appears in the printed record; maximum length is 4000 characters.
Not supported for BillPayment, JournalEntry or Payment. Product: QBW Description: User entered message to the customer.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Note
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Describes the transaction; a private note for the organization that does not appear in the invoice or bill payment. For BillPayment, if payment is made through a check, this note is marked as a memo. The maximum length for Note is 4000 characters.
Not supported for Bill, CashPurchase, Check, or CreditCardCharge. Product: QBW Description: User-entered note about the transaction that does not appear on the invoice.

attributes.name: Status

For Estimate, the values accepted are defined in EstimateStatusEnum, and for BuildAssembly the values are defined in the BuildAssemblyStatusEnum. Product: QBO Description: Supported for Estimate only. The Estimate status may be of the following values:

The range of ItemType is defined in the ItemTypeEnum. If you do not provide the ItemId, the default Service item Id is used.
A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. All other line attributes would be ignored for this shipping line.
For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.
For TimeActivity, this is the Id of the ServiceItem that corresponds to the type of work performed. Required: ALL

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.

For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. For example: "Cash:Cash Drawer".

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.

A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.

Product: QBW Filterable: QBW Description: Indicates the total amount of the object associated. This includes the total of all the charges, allowances and taxes.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Id
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID of the Line Item. Product: QBO Description: ID of the Line Item.
QBO considers a request as an update request for a line item, if you provide an ID that is greater than zero and the ID exists in QBO.
QBO considers a request as an add request for a line item in any of the following conditions: No ID provided, ID provided is less than or equal to zero, ID provided is greater than zero and does not exist in QuickBooks.
Required for updating existing lines.
Not supported for BillPayment, Estimate, Invoice, or Payment. Required: QBO Default-Field: QBW

attributes.name: Desc
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Free form text description of the line item that appears in the printed record. Max. length: 4000 characters. Not supported for BillPayment or Payment. Product: QBW Description: Free form text description of the line item.
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 4095 characters.

attributes.name: GroupMember
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW

attributes.name: CustomField
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Custom Field (or Data Extension).
See Custom Fields.

attributes.name: ItemId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the Item object. A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID for the Item object. Required for Item based expense. For CashPurchase, this is refereced as CashPurchaseLine.ItemId. The range of ItemType is defined in the ItemTypeEnum. If you do not provide the ItemId, the default Service item Id is used.
A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. All other line attributes would be ignored for this shipping line.
For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.
For TimeActivity, this is the Id of the ServiceItem that corresponds to the type of work performed. Required: ALL

attributes.name: ItemName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an item. A fully-qualified name starts with the name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub name; append a colon and sub name for each additional sub name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Discount:Sales:Labor Day".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred.

attributes.name: ItemType
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: Type is an item classification that specifies the use of this item.

attributes.name: ObjectState
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: Indicates which state the object is in currently.

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. If DocNumber is not provided, and the Custom Transaction Number is set to "Off", QBO assigns a document number using the next-in-sequence algorithm for Sales transactions. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 11 characters; for Payment, Bill, ItemReceipt and VendorCredit, max. length: 20 characters. Required: QBW Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: TxnDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred. Often, it is the date when the transaction is created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects the financial statements. If the date is not supplied, the current date on the server is used.
For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. Often, but not required to be, the date the transaction was created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects financial statements. Required: QBW Filterable: ALL Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: Currency
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Currency code based on the ISO 4217 standard that is common to all amounts on the associated transaction.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Msg
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: For an Invoice, this is the user-entered message to the customer that does appear in the invoice, and does appear in the printed invoice. The maximum length for Invoice Msg is 1000 characters.
For a Bill, this is the memo of the transaction to provide more detail, and does not appear in the printed message of the bill. The maximum length for Bill Msg is 4000 characters.
For a CreditCardCharge, this message appears in the printed record; maximum length is 4000 characters.
Not supported for BillPayment, JournalEntry or Payment. Product: QBW Description: User entered message to the customer.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Note
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Describes the transaction; a private note for the organization that does not appear in the invoice or bill payment. For BillPayment, if payment is made through a check, this note is marked as a memo. The maximum length for Note is 4000 characters.
Not supported for Bill, CashPurchase, Check, or CreditCardCharge. Product: QBW Description: User-entered note about the transaction that does not appear on the invoice.

attributes.name: Status
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The status of the associated transaction (the transaction types are described in the TxnTypeEnum). Depending on the transaction type the status may have different values. For example, Sales Transactions acceptable values are defined in PaymentStatusEnum. For Estimate, the values accepted are defined in EstimateStatusEnum, and for BuildAssembly the values are defined in the BuildAssemblyStatusEnum. Product: QBO Description: Supported for Estimate only. The Estimate status may be of the following values:
  • Pending (default)
  • Accepted
  • Rejected
  • Closed

Product: QBO Description: For an Invoice, this is the user-entered message to the customer that does appear in the invoice, and does appear in the printed invoice. The maximum length for Invoice Msg is 1000 characters.
For a Bill, this is the memo of the transaction to provide more detail, and does not appear in the printed message of the bill. The maximum length for Bill Msg is 4000 characters.
For a CreditCardCharge, this message appears in the printed record; maximum length is 4000 characters.
Not supported for BillPayment, JournalEntry or Payment. Product: QBW Description: User entered message to the customer.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Note
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Describes the transaction; a private note for the organization that does not appear in the invoice or bill payment. For BillPayment, if payment is made through a check, this note is marked as a memo. The maximum length for Note is 4000 characters.
Not supported for Bill, CashPurchase, Check, or CreditCardCharge. Product: QBW Description: User-entered note about the transaction that does not appear on the invoice.

attributes.name: Status
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The status of the associated transaction (the transaction types are described in the TxnTypeEnum). Depending on the transaction type the status may have different values. For example, Sales Transactions acceptable values are defined in PaymentStatusEnum. For Estimate, the values accepted are defined in EstimateStatusEnum, and for BuildAssembly the values are defined in the BuildAssemblyStatusEnum. Product: QBO Description: Supported for Estimate only. The Estimate status may be of the following values:
  • Pending (default)
  • Accepted
  • Rejected
  • Closed

attributes.name: CCAccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW				
						Description: ID of the CCAccount object. A reference to the credit card account is required for the Create operation, either the CCAccountId or CCAccountName; CCAccountId is preferred.
						Product: QBO				
						Description: ID of the CCAccount object. Required for the BillPayment if BankAccountId is not specified.
						Required: ALL
						Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: CCAccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for a credit card account. A fully-qualified name starts with the credit card account name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub credit card account name; append a colon and sub credit card account name for each additional sub account (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Fred's Bank Credit Card:Travellers' Club".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the CreditCardAccount is required for the Create operation, either the CCAccountId or TxnNum; CCAccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: EntityId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO
						Description: ID of the entity (Customer, Vendor, or Employee). Required for BillPayment as the ID of the vendor who issued the bill and to whom the payment is made. Optional for CashPurchase, Check, and CreditCardCharge.
						Product: QBW
						Description: ID of the entity (Customer, Vendor, or Employee). A reference to the entity is required for the Create operation, either the EntityId or EntityName; EntityId is preferred.
						Required: All
						Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: EntityName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for the entity. A fully-qualified name starts with the entity name followed by a colon (:), followed by the entity sub name; append a colon and entity sub name for each additional sub entity (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Store54:Shane Hamby".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the entity is required for the Create operation, either the EntityId or EntityName; EntityId is preferred.

attributes.name: EntityType
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The business entity type as defined in the EntityTypeEnum.
Not supported for BillPayment.
Product: QBW Description: The business entity type as defined in the EntityTypeEnum. Required: QBW

attributes.name: TotalAmt
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The total amount (the sum of all lines) of the credit card charge.
Read-only field. Product: QBW Description: The total amount (the sum of all lines) of the credit card charge.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Id
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID of the Line Item. Product: QBO Description: ID of the Line Item.
QBO considers a request as an update request for a line item, if you provide an ID that is greater than zero and the ID exists in QBO.
QBO considers a request as an add request for a line item in any of the following conditions: No ID provided, ID provided is less than or equal to zero, ID provided is greater than zero and does not exist in QuickBooks.
Required for updating existing lines.
Not supported for BillPayment, Estimate, Invoice, or Payment. Required: QBO Default-Field: QBW

attributes.name: Desc
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Free form text description of the line item that appears in the printed record. Max. length: 4000 characters. Not supported for BillPayment or Payment. Product: QBW Description: Free form text description of the line item.
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 4095 characters.

attributes.name: CustomField

Product: QBW Description: Custom Field (or Data Extension).

Product: QBO Description: Total amount of the charges or discounts for the given line. Includes the charges and allowances, but it excludes the tax amount.

attributes.name: ItemId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the Item object. A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID for the Item object. Required for Item based expense. For CashPurchase, this is refereced as CashPurchaseLine.ItemId. The range of ItemType is defined in the ItemTypeEnum. If you do not provide the ItemId, the default Service item Id is used.
A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. All other line attributes would be ignored for this shipping line.
For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.
For TimeActivity, this is the Id of the ServiceItem that corresponds to the type of work performed. Required: ALL

attributes.name: ItemName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an item. A fully-qualified name starts with the name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub name; append a colon and sub name for each additional sub name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Discount:Sales:Labor Day".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred.

attributes.name: ItemType
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: Type is an item classification that specifies the use of this item.

attributes.name: UnitPrice
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW

attributes.name: Qty
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW

			            Description: Indicates the number of order items for the given line. Supported for Item-based expense.

attributes.name: OverrideItemAccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an override item account. A fully-qualified name starts with the name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub name; append a colon and sub name for each additional sub name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Misc Expenses:Tips".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.name: AccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The ID of the Account object.
A reference to the Account is required for the Create operation, either the AccountId or AccountName; AccountId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: Account ID that is associated with the line item.
Account ID is an optional output-only field for the Item based expense.
Account ID is required for the account-based expense.
The account is of the basic five types: Income, Expense, Asset, Liability, Owner equity.
Optional for Item.IncomeAccountRef.AccountId, IncomeAccountRef is specified for sales items. If it is not specified, then the default income account ID from the company's preferences is used.
Optional for Item.ExpenseAccountRef.AccountId, this indicates the expense account that is used to pay the vendor for this item. If this is a service item, it can also be an equity account to record a draw against the company equity to pay for the service. Required: ALL

attributes.name: AccountName

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. If DocNumber is not provided, and the Custom Transaction Number is set to "Off", QBO assigns a document number using the next-in-sequence algorithm for Sales transactions. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 11 characters; for Payment, Bill, ItemReceipt and VendorCredit, max. length: 20 characters. Required: QBW Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: TxnDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred. Often, it is the date when the transaction is created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects the financial statements. If the date is not supplied, the current date on the server is used.
For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. Often, but not required to be, the date the transaction was created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects financial statements. Required: QBW Filterable: ALL Sortable: QBO

			              Description: Amount by which the amount due on the referenced transaction is being reduced. You can specify either DiscountAmt or DiscountRate. If both are specified, DiscountAmt is considered to calculate the amount. Must be specified as a negative amount.
			              Product: QBW
			              Description: Optional amount by which the amount due on the referenced transaction is being reduced.

attributes.name: DiscountRate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Discount percentage by which the amount due on the referenced transaction is being reduced.
For Estimate and Invoice, this is the discount rate in decimal. For example, to apply a 10% discount, specify a value of "0.1" for discount rate.
For SalesReceipt, this is the discount rate specified as a percentage. For example, to apply a 10% discount, specify a value of "10" for discount rate.
You can specify either DiscountAmt or DiscountRate. If both are specified, DiscountAmt is considered to calculate the amount. Product: QBW Description: Optional percentage by which the amount due on the referenced transaction is being reduced.

attributes.name: DiscountAccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
			            Description: ID of the DiscountAccount object. A reference to the DiscountAccount is required for the Create operation, either the DiscountAccountId or DiscountAccountName; DiscountAccountId is preferred.
			            Required: QBW

attributes.name: DiscountAccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an account. A fully-qualified name starts with the account name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub account name; append a colon and sub account name for each additional sub account (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Discount:Sale".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the DiscountAccount is required for the Create operation, either the DiscountAccountId or DiscountAccountName; DiscountAccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: DiscountTaxable
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Whether tax or discount should be applied first on the non line items. If DiscountTaxable is true or null, the tax is applied before the discount is applied on the non-line items. If DiscountTaxable is false, discount is applied before the tax is applied on the non-line items.
Example: Tax=8.5, Discount=-10, Subtotal=100
1. Value=True (apply tax before discount): Total=98.5
2. Value=False (apply discount before tax): Total=97.65 Product: QBW Description: If true, calculate the sales tax first, and then apply the discount. If false, subtract the discount first and then calculate the sales tax.

attributes.name: DocNumber
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Reference number for the transaction. If DocNumber is not provided, and the Custom Transaction Number is set to "Off", QBO assigns a document number using the next-in-sequence algorithm for Sales transactions. Otherwise the value will remain null. Alternatively, you can also pass in "AUTO_GENERATE" in this field to force QBO to auto-sequence the document number for Invoices, Estimates and Sales Receipt. The maximum length for DocNumber is 21 characters. The default value is an empty String. Filter support only provided for Estimate. Product: QBW Description: The primary document number, humanly identifiable, for this transaction.
If it is not provided, QuickBooks business logic will assign the document number using the "next in sequence" algorithm.
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 11 characters; for Payment, Bill, ItemReceipt and VendorCredit, max. length: 20 characters. Required: QBW Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: TxnDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The date entered by the user when this transaction occurred. Often, it is the date when the transaction is created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects the financial statements. If the date is not supplied, the current date on the server is used.
For QuickBooks Online, the Data Type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: The nominal, user entered, date of the transaction. Often, but not required to be, the date the transaction was created in the system. For "posting" transactions, this is the posting date that affects financial statements. Required: QBW Filterable: ALL Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: Currency
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Currency code based on the ISO 4217 standard that is common to all amounts on the associated transaction.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Msg
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: For an Invoice, this is the user-entered message to the customer that does appear in the invoice, and does appear in the printed invoice. The maximum length for Invoice Msg is 1000 characters.
For a Bill, this is the memo of the transaction to provide more detail, and does not appear in the printed message of the bill. The maximum length for Bill Msg is 4000 characters.
For a CreditCardCharge, this message appears in the printed record; maximum length is 4000 characters.
Not supported for BillPayment, JournalEntry or Payment. Product: QBW Description: User entered message to the customer.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Note
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Describes the transaction; a private note for the organization that does not appear in the invoice or bill payment. For BillPayment, if payment is made through a check, this note is marked as a memo. The maximum length for Note is 4000 characters.
Not supported for Bill, CashPurchase, Check, or CreditCardCharge. Product: QBW Description: User-entered note about the transaction that does not appear on the invoice.

attributes.name: Status
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The status of the associated transaction (the transaction types are described in the TxnTypeEnum). Depending on the transaction type the status may have different values. For example, Sales Transactions acceptable values are defined in PaymentStatusEnum. For Estimate, the values accepted are defined in EstimateStatusEnum, and for BuildAssembly the values are defined in the BuildAssemblyStatusEnum. Product: QBO Description: Supported for Estimate only. The Estimate status may be of the following values:
  • Pending (default)
  • Accepted
  • Rejected
  • Closed

attributes.name: CustomerId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The ID of the person or organization that is the end customer receiving the goods or services in the associated transaction. For example, if the transaction is associated with a Job or Project, like "John Doe:Kitchen", this ID must reference "John Doe".
A valid CustomerId or CustomerName is required for the Create request for all AR transactions except SalesReceipt. Product: QBO Description: The ID of the person or organization that is the end customer receiving the goods or services in the associated transaction. For example, if the transaction is associated with a Job or Project, like "John Doe:Kitchen", this ID must reference "John Doe".
For Job Create and Update, if JobParentId is present, this attribute is ignored. If JobParentId is null, this will create the first level job under the specified Customer. For output, the CustomerId shows the root customer.
Required if JobParentId is null.
For SalesReceipt, this is optional, but generally a sales receipt is created for a customer and should specify a CustomerId.
Sort support for SalesReceipt only.
For Job, filter queries first level jobs rooted by specified customer Id. Note that result will not return entire hierarchy.
For TimeActivity, required if TimeActivity.BillableStatus = BillableStatusEnum.BILLABLE. Required: ALL Filterable: QBO Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: CustomerName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for a customer or organization. A fully-qualified name starts with the customer name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub customer name; append a colon and sub customer name for each additional customer name (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Rock Construction:Sammuels".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Customer is required for the Create operation, either the CustomerId (preferred) or CustomerName, for all AR transactions except SalesReceipt. Product: QBO Description: Name of the root customer. Read-only field.
Supported for Job only.

attributes.name: JobId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW

attributes.name: JobName

For example: "Jennifer Hermann:Residential Maintenance:Lawn Mowing".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).

For example: "Jennifer Hermann:Residential Maintenance".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.name: SalesTaxCodeId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the SalesTaxCode object. Product: QBO Description: QBO only supports the customers or jobs being taxable or not, so if this field is "1", the job is taxable. If the field value is null, the job is not taxable. All other values are invalid.
Note that if you have specified a TaxAmt and TaxRate, SalesTaxCodeId will be "1" even if you don't specify it directly. To make SalesTaxCodeId not taxable, TaxAmt and TaxRate must be null.

attributes.name: SalesTaxCodeName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Name for the SalesTaxCode.
Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters. Product: QBO Description: Indicates if the customer or job is taxable. The only valid value is "IS_TAXABLE" indicating the job is taxable. If the field value is null, the job is not taxable. Use SalesTaxCodeId to set the value. This is a read-only field.

attributes.name: PONumber
attributes.synopsis:

Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 13 characters.

attributes.name: FOB
attributes.synopsis:

Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 13 characters.

attributes.name: ShipDate
attributes.synopsis:

Note: For QuickBooks Online, the type is DateTime, not IDSDate. Product: QBW Description: Date for delivery of goods or services.

attributes.name: SubTotalAmt
attributes.synopsis:

Product: QBW Description: Indicates the sub total amount of the object associated. This includes the total of all the charges, and allowances but excludes the amount of tax.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

						Description: ID for the SalesTaxGroup object.

attributes.name: TaxGroupName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Name of the sales tax group.
Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters.

attributes.name: TaxRate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Tax rate reported in percentage (for example, 9.25 - not the fraction 0.0925).
You can specify either TaxAmt or TaxRate. If both are specified, TaxAmt is considered for calculating the amount, and TaxAmt must be equal to the calculated tax based on taxable line amount subtotals, discountTaxable value and TaxRate. Product: QBW Description: The total tax rate used to calculate the tax amount on the transaction. To enter a tax rate of 8.5%, enter 8.5, not 0.085.
Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: TaxAmt
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Indicates the total tax amount for the associated transaction.
You can specify either TaxAmt or TaxRate. If both are specified, TaxAmt is considered for calculating the amount, and TaxAmt must be equal to the calculated tax based on taxable line amount subtotals, discountTaxable value and TaxRate. Product: QBW Description: Indicates the total tax amount for the associated transaction. The subtotal plus the tax amount equals the total amount.
Calculated by QuickBooks business logic; cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: TotalAmt
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Indicates the total amount of the object associated that is overridden by the sum of all the line items. This includes the total of all the charges, allowances and taxes. By default, this is recalculated based on sub items total and overridden. Product: QBW Description: Indicates the total amount of the object associated. This includes the total of all the charges, allowances and taxes.
Calculated by QuickBooks business logic; cannot be written to QuickBooks. Filterable: QBW

attributes.name: ToBePrinted
attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
								Description: If True, the estimate or invoice can be printed. If False or null the estimate or invoice cannot be printed.

attributes.name: ToBeEmailed
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: For Invoice and Estimate, if True, the estimate or invoice can be emailed, and you must provide a value for Header.BillEmail or the request will be rejected. If False or null, the estimate or invoice cannot be emailed.
For SalesReceipt, Specifies whether the sales receipt needs to be sent as an email message. If ToBeEmailed is true, the ToBeEmailed is selected in the UI and the SalesReceipt is readied to be sent as an email message. Note: The API does not support sending email when creating a sales receipt. You will not be able to save the email address through this API and see it in the UI. If you have created a sales recceipt using the QBO UI and if you are using API to view the SalesReceipt, you won’t get the email address info as the element for email address is not supported. However, you can e-mail the sales receipt after creating it; see Sending a SalesReceipt in E-mail, below. Product: QBW Description: If True, the estimate or invoice can be emailed. If False or null, the estimate or invoice cannot be emailed.

attributes.name: Custom
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Free form text.
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 29 characters.

attributes.name: ARAccountId

attributes.name: ARAccountName

A fully-qualified name starts with the account name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub account name; append a colon and sub account name for each additional sub account (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. Most small businesses have a single AR account named "Accounts Receivable"; for a sub account, the fully qualified name would be, for example, "Accounts Receivable:Johnson Trust".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the accounts receivable account is required for the Create operation, either the ARAccountId or ARAccountName; ARAccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: SalesTermId

						Product: QBO

Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters.

attributes.name: BillAddr

attributes.name: ShipAddr

If ShipAddr is not specified, and a default ship-to address is specified in QuickBooks for this customer, the default ship-to address will be used by QuickBooks.

attributes.name: BillEmail

UNSUPPORTED FIELD.

attributes.name: ShipMethodId

attributes.name: ShipMethodName

Product: QBO
			            Description: Name of the shipping method, for example, "UPS".
			            Product: QBW
			            Description: Name of the shipping method, for example, "UPS". Data Services max. length: 256 characters.  QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters.

attributes.name: RemainingCredit
attributes.synopsis:

Cannot be written to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: Detail

UNSUPPORTED FIELD.

			              Product: QBW
			              Description: Optional amount by which the amount due on the referenced transaction is being reduced.

For Estimate and Invoice, this is the discount rate in decimal. For example, to apply a 10% discount, specify a value of "0.1" for discount rate.
For SalesReceipt, this is the discount rate specified as a percentage. For example, to apply a 10% discount, specify a value of "10" for discount rate.
You can specify either DiscountAmt or DiscountRate. If both are specified, DiscountAmt is considered to calculate the amount. Product: QBW Description: Optional percentage by which the amount due on the referenced transaction is being reduced.

For example: "Discount:Sale".

A reference to the DiscountAccount is required for the Create operation, either the DiscountAccountId or DiscountAccountName; DiscountAccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: DiscountTaxable
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Whether tax or discount should be applied first on the non line items. If DiscountTaxable is true or null, the tax is applied before the discount is applied on the non-line items. If DiscountTaxable is false, discount is applied before the tax is applied on the non-line items.
Example: Tax=8.5, Discount=-10, Subtotal=100
1. Value=True (apply tax before discount): Total=98.5
2. Value=False (apply discount before tax): Total=97.65 Product: QBW Description: If true, calculate the sales tax first, and then apply the discount. If false, subtract the discount first and then calculate the sales tax.

attributes.name: ItemId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the Item object. A reference to the Item is required for the Create operation, either the ItemId or ItemName; ItemId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID for the Item object. Required for Item based expense. For CashPurchase, this is refereced as CashPurchaseLine.ItemId. The range of ItemType is defined in the ItemTypeEnum. If you do not provide the ItemId, the default Service item Id is used.
A Shipping Fee can be associated with the transaction by including a line with an ItemId containing a value of "SHIPPING_LINE_ID". When an Item Id of value "SHIPPING_LINE_ID" is passed, only the "Line.Amount" field is used and the value specified in this field is taken as the shipping fee. All other line attributes would be ignored for this shipping line.
For Invoice only, you can also specify a deposit for an invoice by including a line with an ItemId containing the value of "DEPOSIT_LINE_ID". When you specify such as line, "OverrideItemAccountId" is required and you should put the deposit to account id in it. "Line.Amount" will be the deposit amount.
For TimeActivity, this is the Id of the ServiceItem that corresponds to the type of work performed. Required: ALL

For example: "Discount:Sales:Labor Day".

attributes.name: DiscountRatePercent

QBO considers a request as an update request for a line item, if you provide an ID that is greater than zero and the ID exists in QBO.
QBO considers a request as an add request for a line item in any of the following conditions: No ID provided, ID provided is less than or equal to zero, ID provided is greater than zero and does not exist in QuickBooks.

Product: QBW Description: If the line describes the sellable item, the flag indicates whether the line Amount is subject to tax. Product: QBW Description: ID of the Line Item. Product: QBO Description: ID of the Line Item.
QBO considers a request as an update request for a line item, if you provide an ID that is greater than zero and the ID exists in QBO.
QBO considers a request as an add request for a line item in any of the following conditions: No ID provided, ID provided is less than or equal to zero, ID provided is greater than zero and does not exist in QuickBooks.
Required for updating existing lines.
Not supported for BillPayment, Estimate, Invoice, or Payment. Required: QBO Default-Field: QBW

attributes.name: Desc
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: Free form text description of the line item that appears in the printed record. Max. length: 4000 characters. Not supported for BillPayment or Payment. Product: QBW Description: Free form text description of the line item.
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 4095 characters.

attributes.name: GroupMember
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
			            Description: Flag specifying whether the line belongs to a Group Item or Sales Tax group.

attributes.name: CustomField
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Custom Field (or Data Extension).
See Custom Fields.

attributes.name: TxnId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
						Description: ID for the Txn object.

attributes.name: TxnLineId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
						Description: ID for the TxnLine object.

attributes.name: TxnType
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: For information purpose only - the type of the payment transaction.

attributes.name: AccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The ID of the Account object.
A reference to the Account is required for the Create operation, either the AccountId or AccountName; AccountId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: Account ID that is associated with the line item.
Account ID is an optional output-only field for the Item based expense.
Account ID is required for the account-based expense.
The account is of the basic five types: Income, Expense, Asset, Liability, Owner equity.
Optional for Item.IncomeAccountRef.AccountId, IncomeAccountRef is specified for sales items. If it is not specified, then the default income account ID from the company's preferences is used.
Optional for Item.ExpenseAccountRef.AccountId, this indicates the expense account that is used to pay the vendor for this item. If this is a service item, it can also be an equity account to record a draw against the company equity to pay for the service. Required: ALL

attributes.name: AccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an account. A fully-qualified name starts with the account name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub account name; append a colon and sub account name for each additional sub account (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example, "Bad Debt:Loans to Burt".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Account is required for the Create operation, either the AccountId or AccountName; AccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: AccountType
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: Type is an account classification that specifies the use of this account.

attributes.name: EntityId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO
						Description: ID of the entity (Customer, Vendor, or Employee). Required for BillPayment as the ID of the vendor who issued the bill and to whom the payment is made. Optional for CashPurchase, Check, and CreditCardCharge.
						Product: QBW
						Description: ID of the entity (Customer, Vendor, or Employee). A reference to the entity is required for the Create operation, either the EntityId or EntityName; EntityId is preferred.
						Required: All
						Filterable: QBO

attributes.name: EntityName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for the entity. A fully-qualified name starts with the entity name followed by a colon (:), followed by the entity sub name; append a colon and entity sub name for each additional sub entity (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Store54:Shane Hamby".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the entity is required for the Create operation, either the EntityId or EntityName; EntityId is preferred.

attributes.name: EntityType
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBO Description: The business entity type as defined in the EntityTypeEnum.
Not supported for BillPayment.
Product: QBW Description: The business entity type as defined in the EntityTypeEnum. Required: QBW

attributes.name: PaymentMethodId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID for the PaymentMethod object. Product: QBO Description: ID of the PaymentMethod.
For Customer, this is the Id associated with the customer as set in the request, if nothing is set in the request it defaults to null.
For Payment and SalesReceipt, this is the ID of the type of the payment method, such as credit card, cash, and check.
Not supported for Job.

attributes.name: PaymentMethodName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Name of the payment method.
Data Services max. length: 256 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters. Product: QBO Description: Name of the payment method - Cash, Check, AmericanExpress, Visa, MasterCard, etc.
Supported for SalesReceipt only. Read-only field.

attributes.name: ClassId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
			            Description: ID of the Class object.

attributes.name: ClassName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for a class. A fully-qualified name starts with the class name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub class name; append a colon and sub class name for each additional sub class (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Crop:Corn".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).

attributes.name: Amount
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Amount of the deposit.
Required for the Create request if the Deposit is specified as a transfer rather than the payment transaction reference.

attributes.name: CheckNum
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
								Description: Check number.

Product: QBW Description: Unique identifier for an Intuit object across all Intuit internal domains. Required for the Update and Delete operations. Product: QBO Description: Unique identifier for an Intuit object across all Intuit internal domains. Required for the Update and Delete operations.
Filter and Sort support for Bill and BillPayment only. Required: ALL Default-Field: QBW Filterable: QBO Sortable: QBO

attributes.name: SyncToken
attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
							Description: Version number of the object for optimistic locking purposes. Required for the Update and Delete operations.
							Required: ALL

attributes.name: MetaData
attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
							Description: Defines the metadata for the object.

attributes.name: ExternalKey
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW 
							Description: Unique Identifier for an Intuit object that is also associated with an external domain.

attributes.name: Synchronized
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW 
							Description: If true, the data on the cloud has been synchronized with QuickBooks for Windows. If false, the data has been created or updated on the cloud but has not been synchronized with QuickBooks for Windows. Read-only field.

attributes.name: AlternateId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW 
							Description: NOT SUPPORTED. Identifier for an object in the domain of origin, outside of the Intuit domain.

attributes.name: CustomField
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Custom Field (or Data Extension).
See Custom Fields.

attributes.name: Draft
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW 
							Description: Indicates whether the object is in the Draft state, or if it is ready to be written back to QuickBooks.

attributes.name: ObjectState
attributes.synopsis: Product: QBW Description: Indicates which state the object is in currently.

attributes.name: Name
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: User recognizable name for the Discount.
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters.
Required for the Create request. Required: QBW

attributes.name: Desc
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
				                Description: User entered description for the Discount which may include user entered details with reason for the reduction of the amount.

attributes.name: Taxable
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
				                Description: If true, calculate the sales tax first, and then apply the discount. If false, subtract the discount first and then calculate the sales tax.

attributes.name: Active
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
				                Description: Whether or not the discount is active. Inactive discounts may be hidden from display and may not be used on financial transactions.
              				    Required: QBW

attributes.name: Percent
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
				                  Description: Percentage by which the amount due is reduced, from 0% to 100%. To enter a discount of 8.5% use 8.5, not 0.085.

attributes.name: Amount
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
				                  Description: Amount by which the amount due is reduced.

attributes.name: DiscountAccountId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
			            Description: ID of the DiscountAccount object. A reference to the DiscountAccount is required for the Create operation, either the DiscountAccountId or DiscountAccountName; DiscountAccountId is preferred.
			            Required: QBW

attributes.name: DiscountAccountName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an account. A fully-qualified name starts with the account name followed by a colon (:), followed by the sub account name; append a colon and sub account name for each additional sub account (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Discount:Sale".
Data Services max. length: 4000 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 31 characters (single name) or 159 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the DiscountAccount is required for the Create operation, either the DiscountAccountId or DiscountAccountName; DiscountAccountId is preferred.

attributes.name: EmployeeId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID of the Employee object.
A reference to the Employee is required for the Create operation, either the EmployeeId or EmployeeName; EmployeeId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID of the Employee object. Either the VendorId or EmployeeId is required for the TimeActivity. Filterable: QBO Sortable: QBO Required: ALL

attributes.name: EmployeeName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an employee. A fully-qualified name starts with the employee name followed by a colon (:), followed by the employee sub name; append a colon and employee sub name for each additional sub employee (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Store54:Shane Hamby".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Employee is required for the Create operation, either the EmployeeId or EmployeeName; EmployeeId is preferred.

attributes.name: EmployeeId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: ID of the Employee object.
A reference to the Employee is required for the Create operation, either the EmployeeId or EmployeeName; EmployeeId is preferred. Product: QBO Description: ID of the Employee object. Either the VendorId or EmployeeId is required for the TimeActivity. Filterable: QBO Sortable: QBO Required: ALL

attributes.name: EmployeeName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Fully-qualified name for an employee. A fully-qualified name starts with the employee name followed by a colon (:), followed by the employee sub name; append a colon and employee sub name for each additional sub employee (up to five levels) until you have delineated the full name. For example: "Store54:Shane Hamby".
Data Services max. length: 1024 characters. QuickBooks max. length: 41 characters (single name) or 209 characters (fully qualified name).
A reference to the Employee is required for the Create operation, either the EmployeeId or EmployeeName; EmployeeId is preferred.

attributes.name: Id
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Unique identifier for an Intuit object across all Intuit internal domains. Required for the Update and Delete operations. Product: QBO Description: Unique identifier for an Intuit object across all Intuit internal domains. Required for the Update and Delete operations.
Filter and Sort support for Bill and BillPayment only. Required: ALL Default-Field: QBW Filterable: QBO Sortable: QBO

Product: ALL
							Description: Version number of the object for optimistic locking purposes. Required for the Update and Delete operations.
							Required: ALL

attributes.synopsis:
Product: ALL
							Description: Defines the metadata for the object.

attributes.synopsis:

							Description: Unique Identifier for an Intuit object that is also associated with an external domain.

attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW 
							Description: If true, the data on the cloud has been synchronized with QuickBooks for Windows. If false, the data has been created or updated on the cloud but has not been synchronized with QuickBooks for Windows. Read-only field.

attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW 
							Description: NOT SUPPORTED. Identifier for an object in the domain of origin, outside of the Intuit domain.
