Product: QBW Description: Return only objects that exist in the specified Draft state.
See Objects Saved as Draft.

attributes.name: ObjectStateEnable
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: If true, ObjectState is included in each object in the response. Default is false.
Values: ReadOnly, ReadWritable, Errored.

attributes.name: CustomFieldEnable
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Filters the data returned according to the value of a custom field. You may specify up to three CustomFieldQueryParam elements. Multiple CustomFieldQueryParam elements are AND'd.
See Retrieving and Filtering Objects With Custom Fields.

attributes.name: CustomFieldQueryParam
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Filters the data returned according to the value of a custom field. You may specify up to three CustomFieldQueryParam elements. Multiple CustomFieldQueryParam elements are AND'd.
See Retrieving and Filtering Objects With Custom Fields.

attributes.name: CustomFieldFilter
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Filters the data returned according to the value of a custom field. You may specify up to three CustomFieldQueryParam elements. Multiple CustomFieldQueryParam elements are AND'd.
See Retrieving and Filtering Objects With Custom Fields.

attributes.name: CustomFieldDefinitionIdSet
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Filters the data returned according to the value of a custom field. You may specify up to three CustomFieldQueryParam elements. Multiple CustomFieldQueryParam elements are AND'd.
See Retrieving and Filtering Objects With Custom Fields.

attributes.name: StartCreatedTMS
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Use the StartCreatedTMS and EndCreatedTMS attributes to filter for transactions created between these DateTime values.
See Created and Modified Time.

attributes.name: EndCreatedTMS
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Use the StartCreatedTMS and EndCreatedTMS attributes to filter for transactions created between these DateTime values.
See Created and Modified Time.

attributes.name: StartModifiedTMS
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Use the StartModifiedTMS and EndModifiedTMS attributes to filter for transactions modified between these DateTime values.
See Created and Modified Time.

attributes.name: EndModifiedTMS
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: Use the StartModifiedTMS and EndModifiedTMS attributes to filter for transactions modified between these DateTime values.
See Created and Modified Time.

attributes.name: SortByColumn
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW Description: The column (field) for sorting the results.
See Sorting.

attributes.name: TargetRealmId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                            Description: The destination realm (company) for adding a set of custom field definitions,

attributes.name: SetId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                            Description: The unique identifier for a set of custom field definitions.

attributes.name: SetName
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                                Description: The name of a set of custom field definitions.

attributes.name: AuthId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                Description: Must be the Auth Id of the Admin as only administrator is allowed to set up roles.

attributes.name: RoleId
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                Description: The Id of the Customer, Vendor, Employee, or Oher Name that will be used for filtering the objects that belong to that Id.

attributes.name: RoleType
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                Description: The Role Type is ignored in the Add or Mod request as it is derived from the given Role Id.

attributes.name: IteratorId
attributes.synopsis:
Unique identifier for retrieving a batch (chunk) of records in one request. Use a GUID for the value. For use with ChunkSize.
See Traversing Large Result Sets.

attributes.name: StartPage
attributes.synopsis:
Integer that identifies which batch (chunk) of records to return when paging through the results. Default is 1. For use with ChunkSize.
See Traversing Large Result Sets.

attributes.name: ChunkSize
attributes.synopsis:
Number of records returned for one request. The default and max is 500 records. For use with either IteratorId or StartPage.
See Traversing Large Result Sets.

attributes.name: StartTransactionDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                        Description: The start of a date range for when a transaction occurred. The response is filtered by the date, but not by the time. See also EndTransactionDate.

attributes.name: EndTransactionDate
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
                        Description: The end of a date range for when a transaction occurred. The response is filtered by the date, but not by the time. See also StartTransactionDate.

attributes.name: ReportBasis
attributes.synopsis:
Product: QBW
            Description: Specify the basis of the report, Cash or Accrual
